      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(cron): allow empty assistant replies as silent in cron lane",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nFixes #94224 — Cron lane never opts into allowEmptyAssistantReplyAsSilent.\n\n## Problem\n\nCron jobs that intentionally produce empty replies (e.g. silent alert channels — \"watch X, say nothing unless there's something to report\") fail every run with:\n\n```\nFailoverError: CLI backend returned an empty response. (reason: empty_response, lane: \"cron\")\n```\n\nThe underlying CLI returns success, but OpenClaw classifies the empty response as an error because the cron lane never opts into `allowEmptyAssistantReplyAsSilent`.\n\n## Fix\n\n`src/cron/isolated-agent/run-executor.ts` — +2 lines\n\nSet `allowEmptyAssistantReplyAsSilent: true` for both `runCliAgent` and `runEmbeddedAgent` paths in the cron executor. Empty replies from cron jobs are treated as silent success (consistent with pre-2026.6.6 behavior).",
        "branch": "fix/issue-94224-Bug-Cron-lane-never-opts-int",
        "head_sha": "916c4dbc71898f1d23c018c81feb6358ccfb381c",
